00:00:48,755 --> 00:00:58,371
Today we practiced this body care and it's been substantiated by Brian, who's been doing the Reiki.

7
00:00:59,262 --> 00:01:02,968
So I thought we'd have a look at the body from the Buddha's point of view.

8
00:01:11,361 --> 00:01:21,938
So in the Buddha's teachings, the body and mind are two different, for want of a better word, forms of energy, whatever.

9
00:01:23,099 --> 00:01:24,242
But it's not the...

10
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:26,585
It's not the...

11
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,724
awareness, the satipanya, the Buddha within.

12
00:01:29,743 --> 00:01:38,656
This was made more plain in Mahayana, where they talked about the three bodies, Yogacara.

13
00:01:38,677 --> 00:01:47,129
So the first was the body of the Dharma, which is the unconditioned Buddha.

14
00:01:47,709 --> 00:01:56,302
So remember, he said that he had achieved the unconditioned citta, citta here meaning the awareness, he's pointing to the awareness, not the mind.

15
00:01:57,515 --> 00:02:07,614
And there's the Sambhogakaya, which is the body of bliss, which is the mental body, which for the Buddha, of course, becomes one which is heart-based happiness.

16
00:02:08,556 --> 00:02:13,885
Somebody who's fully liberated doesn't suffer as such.

17
00:02:15,789 --> 00:02:19,978
And then there's the Nirmalakaya, which is the body of appearance, which is this physical body.

18
00:02:22,438 --> 00:02:25,421
And this physical body can only give us pain, right?

19
00:02:25,442 --> 00:02:26,563
It can't make us suffer.

20
00:02:27,044 --> 00:02:32,270
The suffering is come because of a wrong relationship to the body, which is identity.

21
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:32,991
It's me.

22
00:02:33,211 --> 00:02:34,292
